snippet.textDisplay:
This will probably get lost in the comments, but I just have a little message because it seems like the majority of people in these comments haven’t had sex/are really uneducated about it.
First, don’t be scared to have sex! It’s a good and natural thing to do! Going off of that, don’t feel obligated to have sex. It’s your body so you choose who you want to do it with and when you want to do it.
Second, ALWAYS use protection. This one is a no brainer—if you’re a girl take the pill or consider getting an IUD (that’s super effective birth control for 5-10 years). I don’t recommend shots, patches, or implants because they have the worst side effects. If you’re dude wear a condom always, unless your partner says otherwise and you’re comfortable with it.
Third, get educated! Planned parenthood is a good place to learn more about safe sex and they can provide you with contraceptives (usually for free). Also, don’t belittle people for their sex (or lack there of) life.
It takes two people to get pregnant so don’t go around calling girls derogatory things because they CHOSE to have sex and you didn’t.
